Class AbstractRegexReplacementRule

java.lang.Object
  edu.northwestern.at.utils.corpuslinguistics.inflector.wordrule.AbstractRegexReplacementRule
All Implemented Interfaces:
WordRule
Direct Known Subclasses:
IrregularMappingRule, RegexReplacementRule
public abstract class AbstractRegexReplacementRule
extends java.lang.Object
implements WordRule

An abstract rule specified using a regular expression and replacement.

Subclasses must implement replace(java.util.regex.Matcher) to perform the actual replacement.

Original code written by Tom White under the Apache v2 license. Modified by Philip R. Burns for integration into MorphAdorner.

disjunction

public static java.lang.String disjunction(java.lang.String[] patterns)
Form the disjunction of the given regular expression patterns.

Parameters:
patterns - An array of regular expression patterns.
Returns:
A pattern that matches if any of the input patterns match.

For example, if "patterns" contains "a" and "b", then the disjunction is "(a|b)", that is, "a or b".
